In Uzbekistan, from March 24, 2020, all non-food markets are closed temporarily in Tashkent Region in accordance with the decision of the administration of the Tashkent region. UPDATE: In Uzbekistan, according to the order of the Special Republican Commission on Prevention of the Covid-19 made on April 25, 2020, following business are allowed to resume their operation:
-Markets for building materials, including business entities involved in retail and wholesale trade in building materials (provided that their area is at least 500 sq.);
- Chain stores of large manufacturers, designed to sell their own products (in compliance with the sanitary standard of 10 square meters per 1 buyer);
- Craftsmen - sale in the places (stores) of products created by them, separate from markets;
- Business entities (of any form of ownership) engaged in the cultivation and sale of seeds and seedlings;
- Entrepreneurs (regardless of ownership) engaged in the sale of automotive parts.

In Uzbekistan, according to the news report on March 25, 2020, public service centers, registry offices and notaries will be open for emergencies only:
- public service centers assist citizens online and provide service in emergencies only;
- registry offices are open only to register births or deaths;
- notaries assist only with the will, power of attorney, deposit and mortgage-related issues.
